\contentsline {subsubsection}{3.4 System Evaluation and Validation Criteria}{66}{section*.120}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{This section defines the evaluation and validation criteria derived directly from the identified business, user, and system requirements. These criteria establish a structured basis for assessing whether the proposed framework meets its intended objectives. In accordance with IEEE practices, the criteria are specified at a high level and are used later to guide system validation and performance evaluation, without presenting implementation results at this stage.}{66}{section*.121}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{The evaluation criteria are grouped into functional effectiveness, performance efficiency, risk and security impact, and usability and collaboration.}{66}{section*.122}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.1 Functional Validation Criteria}{66}{section*.123}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria evaluate the system’s ability to fulfill its intended functional requirements:}{66}{section*.124}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Threat-to-Test Mapping Accuracy: The system shall correctly map identified threat scenarios to relevant penetration testing techniques and attack vectors.}{66}{section*.125}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Threat Coverage: The system shall ensure that all high-risk threats identified during threat modeling are addressed through corresponding penetration tests.}{66}{section*.126}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Traceability: The system shall maintain clear traceability between assets, threats, vulnerabilities, test cases, and mitigation strategies.}{66}{section*.127}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Automation Effectiveness: The system shall reduce reliance on manual configuration during threat analysis and penetration testing activities.}{66}{section*.128}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.2 Performance and Efficiency Criteria}{66}{section*.129}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria assess the operational efficiency of the proposed framework:}{66}{section*.130}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Time Efficiency: The system shall reduce the time required to plan and execute security assessments compared to traditional isolated approaches.}{66}{section*.131}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Responsiveness: The system shall update threat models and risk scores promptly following penetration testing activities or threat intelligence updates.}{66}{section*.132}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Scalability Support: The system shall handle increasing numbers of assets, threats, and test cases without significant degradation in performance.}{66}{section*.133}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.3 Risk and Security Effectiveness Criteria}{66}{section*.134}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria measure the system’s effectiveness in supporting risk-driven security decision-making:}{67}{section*.135}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Risk Prioritization Accuracy: The system shall correctly prioritize threats and vulnerabilities based on impact, likelihood, and exploitability.}{67}{section*.136}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Adaptive Risk Management: The system shall demonstrate the ability to adapt to emerging threats through continuous feedback and threat intelligence integration.}{67}{section*.137}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Improved Risk Visibility: The system shall provide clear and actionable visual representations of risk levels to support informed security decisions.}{67}{section*.138}%
\contentsline {paragraph}{3.4.4 Usability and Collaboration Criteria}{67}{section*.139}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{These criteria evaluate how effectively the system supports user interaction and teamwork:}{67}{section*.140}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Ease of Use: The system shall provide intuitive interfaces that allow users to perform core security tasks with minimal training.}{67}{section*.141}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Collaboration Support: The system shall facilitate effective collaboration through shared documentation, notifications, and role-based access control mechanisms.}{67}{section*.142}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{Report Clarity: The system shall generate clear, structured, and understandable reports suitable for both technical and non-technical stakeholders.}{67}{section*.143}%
\contentsline {subsubsection}{3.5 Chapter Summary}{67}{section*.144}%
